    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SCHOOL SPENDING</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By KAREN DEMASTERS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Census Bureau reports that New Jersey spent $9,461 per student on education during 1997, ranking state second behind New York by nearly $1,000; national average is $5,873 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>New Jersey spent the most money per student on education during 1997, outspending the second ranked state, New York, by nearly $1,000, according to a Census Bureau report released last week. In that year, the last for which numbers are available, New Jersey spent $9,461 for each student, compared with a national spending average of $5,873.</p>
        <p>KAREN DeMASTERS</p>
      </block>
